<header class="entry-header">
<h1 class="entry-title">Project Overview</h1> </header>
<div class="content"><p><strong><a href="https://projects.511wi.gov/wis76cirshioc/wp-content/uploads/sites/1025/2map76.jpg"><img alt="" class="wp-image-25 alignright" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="454" sizes="(max-width: 588px) 100vw, 588px" src="https://projects.511wi.gov/wis76cirshioc/wp-content/uploads/sites/1025/2map76-1024x791.jpg" srcset="https://projects.511wi.gov/wis76cirshioc/wp-content/uploads/sites/1025/2map76-1024x791.jpg 1024w, https://projects.511wi.gov/wis76cirshioc/wp-content/uploads/sites/1025/2map76-300x232.jpg 300w, https://projects.511wi.gov/wis76cirshioc/wp-content/uploads/sites/1025/2map76-768x593.jpg 768w, https://projects.511wi.gov/wis76cirshioc/wp-content/uploads/sites/1025/2map76-1536x1187.jpg 1536w, https://projects.511wi.gov/wis76cirshioc/wp-content/uploads/sites/1025/2map76-577x446.jpg 577w, https://projects.511wi.gov/wis76cirshioc/wp-content/uploads/sites/1025/2map76-500x386.jpg 500w, https://projects.511wi.gov/wis76cirshioc/wp-content/uploads/sites/1025/2map76-110x85.jpg 110w, https://projects.511wi.gov/wis76cirshioc/wp-content/uploads/sites/1025/2map76.jpg 1650w" width="588"/></a></strong></p>
<p><strong> 2024 CONSTRUCTION BEGINS APRIL 29, 2024.</strong></p>
<ul>
<li aria-hidden="true">Full closures of WIS 22 at US 45 begins April 29.</li>
<li>Full closure of WIS 76 between US 45 and WIS 54 begins May 9.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Project locations</strong></p>
<p>The WIS 76 improvements are separated into three individual projects that extend from WIS 54 in the village of Shiocton to the US 45/WIS 76/WIS 22 intersection west of the village of Bear Creek in the towns of Bovina, Liberty, Maple Creek and Deer Creek in the counties of Outagamie and Waupaca. Each project is identified by a unique Project​​​ ID.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Waupaca County project:</strong> Outagamie/Waupaca County Line to US 45 (Project ID 6518-00-70)</li>
<li><strong>Outagamie County project</strong>: WIS 54 to Outagamie/Waupaca County Line (Project ID 6518-06-71)</li>
<li><strong>Outagamie County bridge project:</strong> Bridge structures between Boelter​ Road and County W (Project ID 6518-07-71). Complete 2023.
<ul>
<li>WisDOT created a project exhibit showing locations of all three projects on a color-coded display map:
<ul>
<li><a href="https://wisconsindot.gov/Documents/projects/by-region/ne/76shiocton/map2.pdf">View all project on WIS 76 projects exhibit</a></li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Project benefits</strong></p>
<p>The existing pavement is showing signs of distress including traverse cracking and the existing joints are failing. The purpose of the project is to improve the deteriorating pavement and structures on WIS 76, extend the roadway’s service life, decrease maintenance costs, and upgrade other roadway deficiencies to improve safety.   Intersection modifications will provide improved turning movements and increase safety.</p>
<p><strong>Project improvements</strong>​​</p>
<p>Project ID 6518-00-70 (Waupaca County: County Line to US 45)</p>
<ul>
<li>Mill/overlay of the existing pavement</li>
<li>Realigning median islands on WIS 76/WIS 22 at US 45 intersection</li>
<li>Widening for an improved right turn lane on WIS 22 at US 45 intersection</li>
<li>Pavement markings and shoulder gravel</li>
</ul>
<p>Project ID 6518-06-71 (Outagamie County: WIS 54 to County Line)</p>
<ul>
<li>Mill/overlay of existing pavement</li>
<li>Culvert replacements (complete 2023)</li>
<li>Beamguard replacements</li>
<li>Curb ramp replacements within the village of Bear Creek</li>
<li>Pavement markings and shoulder gravel</li>
</ul>
<p>Project ID 6518-07-71 (Outagamie County bridges)</p>
<ul>
<li>Replace two existing bridges with box culverts (complete 2023)</li>
<li>Pavement markings and shoulder gravel (complete 2023)</li>
</ul>
<p>Please see our project design display showing locations of specific construction operations:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://wisconsindot.gov/Documents/projects/by-region/ne/76shiocton/76display.pdf">View WIS 76 project design display</a></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Project schedule</strong></p>
<div>
<div>Construction is scheduled to resume on April 29, 2024 and finish in summer 2024.</div>
</div>
<div></div>
<div><!-- SEO optimization --><strong>Traffic impacts</strong></div>
<div>
<ul>
<li><strong>Full closure of WIS 22 at US 45 begins April 29, 2024. </strong></li>
<li class="auto-3557" data-id="58114"><strong>Full closure of WIS 76 between US 45 and WIS 54 begins May 9, 2024.</strong></li>
</ul>
</div>
<p>Full closures, lane closures, and flagging operations will be utilized at various times during construction. Construction will be staged in a manner to minimize traffic disruptions. Access to businesses and property owners will always be maintained.</p>
<ul>
<li>Beginning May 6, 2024: WIS 76 will be detoured for the culvert, paving and structure replacement work.
<ul>
<li>The detour will follow WIS 54 and US 45.</li>
<li><a class="auto-5521" href="https://projects.511wi.gov/wis76cirshioc/wp-content/uploads/sites/1025/76detour.pdf">View WIS 76 detour route in display map</a></li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>Beginning April 29, 2024: The west leg of US 45/WIS 76/WIS 22 will be closed for intersection improvements. WIS 22 will be detoured for 45 days.
<ul>
<li>The detour route will utilize County T and County O.</li>
<li><a href="https://projects.511wi.gov/wis76cirshioc/wp-content/uploads/sites/1025/22detour.pdf">View WIS 22 detour route in display map</a></li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>Traffic control in the form of flagging operations will be used to close one lane at a time in portions of the work zone.</li>
<li>Businesses affected by the detours are urged to use the resources noted below for businesses in work zones.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong data-id="85527"><a href="https://projects.511wi.gov/wis76cirshioc/wp-content/uploads/sites/1025/bizpic.jpg" rel="https://wisconsindot.gov/Pages/projects/in-together/default.aspx noopener" target="_blank"><img alt="" class="alignright wp-image-42" decoding="async" height="226" sizes="(max-width: 266px) 100vw, 266px" src="https://projects.511wi.gov/wis76cirshioc/wp-content/uploads/sites/1025/bizpic.jpg" srcset="https://projects.511wi.gov/wis76cirshioc/wp-content/uploads/sites/1025/bizpic.jpg 300w, https://projects.511wi.gov/wis76cirshioc/wp-content/uploads/sites/1025/bizpic-100x85.jpg 100w" width="266"/></a>Temporary business signing and business resources</strong></p>
<p>Temporary business signing may be placed during the detoured portion of the project by filling out a WisDOT business signing permit. All temporary business signing needs approval via the permit before placement to ensure it is in a safe location and does not pose a visual distraction or traffic hazard. The temporary business signing permit is free. Costs associated with creating the temporary sign are the responsibility of the business. The permit is available as a fillable-form WORD document or pdf below, or you can request one from the project contacts below.</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://projects.511wi.gov/wis76cirshioc/wp-content/uploads/sites/1025/businesssignpermit.docx">Download Temporary Business Sign Permit</a> (Fillable-form WORD)</li>
<li><a href="https://projects.511wi.gov/wis76cirshioc/wp-content/uploads/sites/1025/businesssignpermit.pdf">Download Temporary Business Sign Permit</a> (PDF)
<ul>
<li>Please email or mail the free permit to any of the contacts below.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p>For more information regarding temporary signing, plus tips and tools for businesses impacted by highway construction, please visit WisDOT’s “In This Together” business resource website. The In This Together program is offered to business and community leaders as an idea source as they plan for road construction in their area.</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://wisconsindot.gov/Pages/projects/in-together/default.aspx">Visit WisDOT’s In This Together Website</a></li>
</ul>
